Foreign Acquisitions Surge 20-Fold on Shanghai Asset Exchange

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-25T10:44:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/foreign-acquisitions-surge-20-fold-on-shanghai-asset-exchange.html
Acquisitions by foreign buyers on
the Shanghai United Assets and Equity Exchange increased by
almost 20-fold in the first quarter from a year earlier to 4.36
billion yuan ($668 million), according to  a statement  posted on
the Shanghai city governmentâ€™s website today.  Transactions conducted by foreign sellers more than doubled
in the first quarter from a year earlier to 1.03 billion yuan,
according to the statement. The value of transactions involving
state-owned enterprises fell 26 percent to 15.4 billion yuan in
the period, according to the statement.  --Regina Tan. Editor: John Liu  To contact Bloomberg News staff on this story:
